snippet.textDisplay:
it really hurts for fans because it puts a bad name on the original musical, which a lot of people, including myself, have deeply fond memories of. my mother used to read me t.s. eliot as a child, and i was always so excited to watch the musical on tape. the almost nonsensical, whimsical, wordplay-filled songs and the beautiful choreo really entranced me as a kid. but hollywood has taken something that is special to people for a multitude of reasons, put it in a spotlight, and shat all over it.


i saw a few people in the comments talk about how the furry fandom and cats fans have next to no overlap, which to be honest i don't care about either way. but unfortunately, because pop culture right now likes to use furries as the butt of a joke, cats being thrust into public eye has, in general, made it an easy target for ridicule. having it become disrespected and nothing more than a joke is my worst fear, and i wish it could've stayed in history and not insulted by this hollywood bastardization. for people who have been fans of the theater production, especially those who had it as a part of their childhood, it's heartbreaking to see it twisted like this, without any real soul and dying as a flopped cash grab.

snippet.textDisplay:
Cats The Musical is not something you can make a coherent movie out of. All the musical is cats introducing themselves until one of them gets chosen to die or something along those lines. It's very fun to watch in the theatre! I think the whole production is on YouTube somewhere.
But Cats 2019. Dear God. I named my kitten Mr. Mistoffelees after Cats THE MUSICAL. Now I regret everything I have ever done. I wish Spielberg's 2D animated Cats adaptation somehow made it. Here's the thing too, THEY DIDNT MOCAP A LOT OF IT APPARENTLY WHICH MEANS HEY YOU HAD EVERY OPPORTUNITY TO NOT MAKE THEM LOOK LIKE THAT. Even with a more actual cat-like design you can still reference the dancers!! I would have redesigned all of your characters for FREE with how awful these look! They have HUMAN NOSES, BOOBS??, AND WHAT THE FUCK IS UP WITH THE EARS LIKE THAT???
Cats is good as a little fun musical about quirky cats, Cats 2019 is a war crime.

snippet.textDisplay:
For those of you who don’t know, this movie is based on a Broadway musical that is based on a book of nonsensical poems about cats. In the musical there is no real plot, but it’s fun to watch, the costumes are amazing, and the set is incredibly detailed. I highly recommend that you go watch it.

The story of how the musical came to be is also interesting.
—

Please, spread this knowledge. More people should know about the musical and just how much better it is from this dumpster-fire of a movie. It’s a Broadway Classic and deserves more attention.
snippet.textOriginal:
For those of you who don’t know, this movie is based on a Broadway musical that is based on a book of nonsensical poems about cats. In the musical there is no _real_ plot, but it’s fun to watch, the costumes are amazing, and the set is *_incredibly_* detailed.  I highly recommend that you go watch it.

The story of how the musical came to be is also interesting.
—

Please, spread this knowledge. More people should know about the musical and just how much better it is from this dumpster-fire of a movie. It’s a Broadway _Classic_ and deserves more attention.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think it's really sad that this bad production is making people hate cats the musicle in general.. I encourage everyone to watch the taped London production with Elaine Paige as Grizabella, which is wonderful. It also needs to be understood that cats is revue-like, so when you feel like there isn't really a story being told for most of the film that's because that's not what's trying to be done.
I think the london production just generally captures the vibe of the musical better, so you kind of naturally understand it, while this new film just leaves you confused and leads the musical in directions it isn't supposed to go.
